        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-02T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-02T14:00:00-05:00" n="503" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–2548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-02T15:00:00-04:00">July 2, 1948—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>973. NAC agencies including ECA by unanimous informal vote today agreed to
                    previous NAC recommendation re Article VII (new Article V) para 5 (Embtel 1149
                    June 25 <hi rend="italic">et seq</hi>.) with following amendment interpolated
                    between “The Government of China” and “shall hold the remaining balance”: “in
                    agreement with the Government of the United States”. Emb should therefore
                    substitute NAC language transmitted Deptel 900 June 19 including this amendment
                    (Note Dept comment Deptel 920 June 24). Dept anticipates no Chinese objection
                    new language this section.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
